# Architecture Plan (Issues #1-#14)

## 1) Module Structure and File Organization

- App framework: Next.js App Router with TypeScript.
- UI system: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components.
- Data layer: Prisma ORM with SQLite.
- Auth: simple admin auth using server action + cookie/session guard via middleware.

Proposed top-level structure:

- `app/`
  - `(public)/`
    - `layout.tsx` (shared public header/footer)
    - `page.tsx` (home, paginated list)
    - `post/[slug]/page.tsx` (detail)
  - `(admin)/admin/`
    - `login/page.tsx`
    - `page.tsx` (dashboard)
    - `posts/new/page.tsx`
    - `posts/[id]/edit/page.tsx`
  - `api/` (optional if needed; prefer server actions where practical)
  - `sitemap.ts`
  - `robots.ts`
  - `layout.tsx` (root)
  - `globals.css`

- `components/`
  - `ui/` (shadcn generated components)
  - `admin/` (post table, editor form, delete confirmation)
  - `public/` (post list, pagination, metadata helpers)

- `lib/`
  - `prisma.ts` (singleton client)
  - `auth.ts` (session helpers, password verify)
  - `posts.ts` (post queries, pagination, CRUD utilities)
  - `markdown.ts` (parse/render/sanitize helpers)
  - `env.ts` (typed env reads)

- `prisma/`
  - `schema.prisma`
  - `migrations/`

- `types/`
  - `post.ts` (DTO/view models)
  - `auth.ts`

- `tests/`
  - `e2e/` (Playwright scenarios)

- Root config/files:
  - `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.env.example`

## 2) Shared Types

- `PostSummary`: id, slug, title, excerpt, createdAt, updatedAt.
- `PostDetail`: `PostSummary` + markdown body/html body.
- `PostFormInput`: title, slug, content, published.
- `PaginatedPosts`: items, page, pageSize, totalItems, totalPages.
- `AuthSession`: authenticated flag + minimal admin identity.

## 3) Dependencies Between Issues

- #1 is base for all.
- #2 depends on #1 and is prerequisite for #6-#10, #12-#14.
- #3 can be done after #1; ideally before #14.
- #4 depends on #1; #5 depends on #4.
- #6 depends on #2 and #5.
- #7 depends on #2, #5, #6.
- #8 depends on #6/#7.
- #9 depends on #2.
- #10 depends on #2 and #9 data conventions (slug/detail route).
- #11 should be in place before finalizing #9/#10 UX.
- #12 depends on #9/#10/#11 content structure.
- #13 depends on #9/#10 routing and metadata assumptions.
- #14 depends on all prior issues and stable Docker/runtime setup.

## 4) Key Design Decisions

- Use App Router server components for read-heavy pages (home/detail/dashboard), server actions for admin mutations/auth where possible.
- Keep Prisma access centralized in `lib/posts.ts` + `lib/prisma.ts` to avoid query duplication.
- Use slug as public identifier; numeric id remains internal for admin editing/deleting.
- Markdown pipeline should sanitize output before rendering to avoid XSS.
- Auth should use HTTP-only secure cookie with middleware route protection for `/admin/*` except `/admin/login`.
- Metadata generation should be route-level (`generateMetadata`) with consistent OG image/title/description fallback strategy.
- `sitemap.ts` and `robots.ts` generated from canonical site URL env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`).
- E2E suite should cover auth flow, CRUD happy path, public list/detail rendering, SEO endpoints (`/sitemap.xml`, `/robots.txt`).
